These two poemS, by the way, illustrate the type of sonnet that is probably earliest: two rimes alternating through the first eight lines; in the last six, three rimeS, running cde cde.

For his sonnet-debate Dante had, then, abundant precedent in the literature of his century. His theme, however, was not a literary one: it , was rather a discussion of Love — the favorite topic among the trouba· dourS, who were apt to treat it in the more formal type of tenso known as partimen or joc partit, a debating game.
